'''Allah Rakha Rahman''' (en [[luenga tamil|tamil]] ''ஏ.ஆர்.ரகுமான்'') es un compositor, produtol, músicu i cantanti [[La Índia|índiu]]. 

== Via ==
Tuvu nacéncia el 6 de [[Jeneru]] de 1966 i le didun el nombri de '''A. S. Dileep Kumar'''. La su carrera comu compositor de música de cini escomençó enos prencípius la décaa los 90. Á ganau dos [[Prémius Óscar|Oscars]], trezi [[prémius Filmfare]], quatru Nacional Film Aware de la Índia, un prémiu BAFTA un Golden Globe.<ref>http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/4179888.cms|title=It's a bridge for Indian cinema: A R Rahman|work=[[Times of India]]|accessdate=26 February 2008}}</ref> He has also been nominated for two [[Grammy Award]]s.<ref name=NDTV>{{cite web|title= Two Grammy nominations for AR Rahman|publisher=[[NDTV]]|date=3 December 2009|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?Section=Movies&ID=ENTEN20090119572&subcatg=MOVIESINDIA&keyword=bollywood|accessdate=2009-12-03}}</ref>

Working in [[Cinema of India|India's various film industries]], [[international cinema]] and [[theatre]], by 2003, Rahman, in a career spanning over a decade, has sold more than 100 million records of his [[film scores]] and [[Film soundtracks|soundtracks]] worldwide,<ref name="selling">{{cite web | title=Indian film composer for Rings| work=[[BBC]]| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3211258.stm| year=2003| accessdate=15 November 2008 | date=2003-10-21}}</ref> and sold over 200 million cassettes,<ref name="release">{{cite web | author=Das Gupta, Surajeet|coauthors=Sen, Soumik|title=Composing a winning score| work=[[Rediff]]| url=http://www.rediff.com/money/2002/sep/21bizsp.htm| accessdate=15 November 2008}}</ref> making him one of the world's [[List of best-selling music artists|all-time top selling recording artists]].

''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine has referred to him as the "Mozart of Madras" and several Tamil commentators have coined him the nickname ''Isai Puyal'' (Tamil: இசைப் புயல்; English: ''Music Storm'').<ref>[http://specials.msn.co.in/sp08/oscar/rahman.asp All About Rahman - Oscars 2009 Special]</ref> In 2009, the magazine placed Rahman in the [[Time 100]] list of 'World's Most Influential People'.<ref>[http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,1894410_1893836_1894435,00.html The 2009 TIME 100 - A.R. Rahman] [[TIME]].</ref>

